  "profile": {
    "summary": "Elena Volkov is a 29-year-old Ukrainian freelance translator and interpreter based in Kyiv. She is fluent in Ukrainian, Russian, English, and Polish, with a background in philology from Taras Shevchenko National University. Elena specializes in literary fiction and legal documents, and also interprets for international journalists and NGOs. She actively uses her English blog to raise global awareness about Ukrainian literature. Facing wartime anxieties, Elena finds solace and expresses herself through poetry writing, traditional embroidery, and volunteering for a charity supporting frontline civilians.",
